text: Edsbyns IF is a sports club in Edsbyn in Sweden. The club was established on 6 June 1909 and adopted the game of bandy in 1925. It won the Swedish national men's championship in the years of 1952, 1953, 1962, 1978, 2004, 2005, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2017, 2018, 2020 and 2022.. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:1909 establishments in Europe Category:Bandy clubs in Sweden Category:1900s establishments in Sweden
